==English==
===Etymology===
Origin uncertain; it may have come from a resemblance to the coat of arms of [[w:John Dalrymple, 1st Earl of Stair|Dalrymple, Lord Stair]], who was an object of criticism for his part in the [[w:Massacre of Glencoe|Massacre of Glencoe]] in 1692, and his work in bringing about the Union with England in 1707 (ref. Oxford English Dictionary, 2nd edition 1989).

